attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit MSB executable, PowerPC or cisco 4500, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

threat_severity.level_description: Severity MEDIUM because it was considered trojan.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a DDoS botnet agent, likely a variant of the Gafgyt (Bashlite) or Mirai families. It features multiple malicious behaviors including anti-virtualization checks by searching for 'VMware' in '/sys/class/dmi/id/product_name', singleton instance enforcement via the lock file '/tmp/.bot_lock', and process enumeration through '/proc' to identify and potentially terminate rival bot processes. The sample contains explicit command-parsing logic for various DDoS attack vectors, evidenced by command strings like '!syn', '!ack', '!http', '!udpplain', and '!icmp'. It also includes hardcoded HTTP request templates and a standard browser User-Agent string used for web-based flooding attacks. Function 'sub_10001820' implements custom data obfuscation, a common technique for hiding C2 configuration.
